      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence study must demonstrate that discretization error in hemolysis index QoI is below 10% using at least three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (2.1M, 5.8M, 14.2M cells) were evaluated. Richardson extrapolation yields a GCI of 6.3% on the normalized hemolysis index at the worst-case operating point. Discretization error is within the 10% acceptance threshold. Required level 2 is met."
