      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) must agree with experimental measurements within combined experimental and numerical uncertainty bands at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values fall within the experimental uncertainty envelope at 4 of 5 operating points; the fifth point deviates by 8.1%, within the combined uncertainty estimate of 12%. Relative hemolysis index RH < 1 at worst-case condition. Required level 2 is met."
