      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (NIH, scalar shear stress, residence time) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint (hemolysis) and to the device decision (tolerance selection).",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis, which is the regulatory-accepted metric for blood damage in pump assessments. Secondary QoIs (volume-averaged scalar shear stress and blood element residence time) are established surrogates for hemolysis risk. Direct linkage to clinical endpoint and tolerance decision is documented. Required level 2 is met."
